    <IRS990ScheduleO documentId="RetDoc1044400001">
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART III, LINE 3</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE ORGANIZATION CLOSED ONE OF OUR DETOX PROGRAMS, SHAMIA, IN OCTOBER 2023.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE CFO REVIEWS AND SIGNS THE FORM 990 BEFORE IT IS FILED.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>YES, THERE IS REGULAR AND CONSISTENT MONITORING ON COMPLIANCE TO THE POLICY. INDEPENDENT CONTRACTORS ARE ALWAYS CHECKED REGARDING ANY RELATIONSHIP EXISTING BETWEEN THEM AND ANY OFFICER, DIRECTOR OR EMPLOYEE OF THE COMPANY. ALL OFFICERS, DIRECTORS AND EMPLOYEES ARE REMINDED OF THIS POLICY WHEN SELECTING ANY INDEPENDENT CONTRACTOR.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>YES, A PROCESS HAS BEEN ESTABLISHED FOR DETERMINING THE COMPENSATION OF THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR OR CEO OF THE ORGANIZATION. BOARD OFFICERS ARE NON-COMPENSATED. BI-BETT HAS DEVELOPED A STANDARD CAREER LADDER AND POLICY TO WHICH ALL EMPLOYEES OF THE COMPANY ARE SUBJECT, WHICH IS APPROVED ANNUALLY BY THE BOARD.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>AS A NON-PROFIT, BI-BETT ALWAYS COMPLIES WITH THE REQUIREMENT TO SUBMIT FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, PERTINENT DOCUMENTS AND OUR CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY TO VARIOUS COUNTIES, TO THE STATE OF CALIFORNIA, VARIOUS FINANCIAL INSTITUTIONS, THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT AND OTHER GOVERNMENT AGENCIES WHO HAVE INTEREST IN THE CORPORATION. THE CORPORATION ALWAYS RESPONDS TO REQUESTS FOR SUCH DOCUMENTS FROM THE PUBLIC.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART XI, LINE 9:</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>TRANSFER UHI NET ASSETS TO BI-BETT 502,593.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART XII, LINE 2C:</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE CFO, BOARD TREASURER AND ONE OTHER BOARD MEMBER MEETS WITH THE AUDITORS BEFORE THE AUDITED FINANCIALS ARE SIGNED.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
